<div style="background-color:whitesmoke; opacity: 0.96; height: 1400px; padding-top: 20px; margin-right: 60px; margin-left: 60px; padding-right: 40px; padding-left: 40px; border: 1px solid black;">
<p1 style="font-family:georgia, verdana, sans-serif;font-size:300%;"><center><u>Interactive Map</u></center></p1><br>
<div id="mapid" style="width:1120px; height:1200px;margin-right: auto;margin-left: auto;">
<div id="slide-in">
<h3><center><u>Map Instructions</u></center></h3>
<p><center>This interactive map allows you to explore the data and our findings, enabling you to directly visualise the carbon concentration and deprivation in Edinburgh. This map contains the final data from our analysis, as well as data from the Scottish Index of Multiple Deprivation (<a href="https://simd.scot/#/simd2020/BTTTFTT/9/-4.0000/55.9000/">SIMD</a>). Use this map to navigate the findings of the different datazones (neighbourhoods) in Edinburgh, including using the search feature to locate a specific address or postcode of your choice.</center></p>
<h4><center>The Basemaps</center></h4>
<p><center>Choose between the automated grayscale map or the streets of Edinburgh map as your basemap for which to overlay the data layers.</center></p>
<h4><center>The Data Layers</center></h4>
<p><center>The SIMD layer details the overall deprivation rank for each datazone, as well as the individual rankings for the 7 factors that determine 'deprivation'. The Carbon Stock Concentration layer details the number of trees in each greenspace, as well as the carbon concentration in tons and kg/m<sup>2</sup>. The Far-Deprived Datazone layer shows the neighbourhoods in Edinburgh that are both too far (over 1km) away from a high value carbon greenspace and fall within the bottom 20% percentile in the SIMD.</center></p>
</div>
<button id="advanced">Map Instructions</button>
</div>
</div>
